snippet: The Labor Department said import prices fell 0.5 percent last month after declining 0.6 percent in September. They have now fallen in 14 of the last 16 months.
abstract: Labor Dept reports import prices dropped by 0.5 percent in October, indication of strong dollar and soft global demand; Commerce Dept reports wholesale inventories rose 0.5 percent in September, which suggests initial impressions of abruptness of slowdown in economic growth were overstated.
lead_paragraph: The Labor Department said import prices fell 0.5 percent last month after declining 0.6 percent in September. They have now fallen in 14 of the last 16 months.

headline.main: Import Prices Fall on Weakness in Oil, and Wholesale Inventories Show Gains
headline.print_headline: Import Prices Fall on Weakness in Oil, and Wholesale Inventories Show Gains
